## ☕ What this PR adds
This PR adds a new JSON sample file — `south_indian_filter_coffee.json` — under `data/samples/`.

## 📋 Details
- Contains structured data for South Indian Filter Coffee
- Includes metadata such as cuisine, difficulty, prep time, nutrition facts, etc.
- Follows the same schema as `masala_chai.json`
- Ready for integration with Java-based data parsers or APIs

## ✅ Why this addition
Adds variety to the existing recipe samples with a new traditional Indian beverage. Perfect for demonstrating JSON parsing and object mapping in Java advanced programs.

## 🧪 How to use
Use with your Java JSON parsing example:
```java
import com.google.gson.Gson;
import java.io.FileReader;

public class ParseCoffee {
  public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
    Gson gson = new Gson();
    Coffee coffee = gson.fromJson(new FileReader("data/samples/south_indian_filter_coffee.json"), Coffee.class);
    System.out.println("Recipe: " + coffee.title);
  }
}
